  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "skYsbam67xpivoG3DJG/nzSLlK4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# window.ph.swarm Plugin Surface\n\nThe browser plugin in `src/plugin/init.ts` exposes Swarm runtime status to the Connect settings UI via the global `window.ph.swarm` object. This is the contract between the adapter core and the Connect-side settings UI components.\n\nThe plugin is responsible for:\n\n- **Bee detection** \u2014 probing the configured Bee endpoint (default `localhost:1633`) and surfacing connectivity state\n- **Stamp management** \u2014 status queries, top-up, expand, and create operations over the `/stamps` HTTP API\n- **Wallet integration** \u2014 triggering `personal_sign` for deterministic key derivation via `wallet-signer.ts`\n- **Event emission** \u2014 sync progress, stamp expiry warnings, and connection state changes\n\nA companion module `src/plugin/sharing.ts` implements cross-user encrypted sharing and import flows (drive bundles between sender and recipient addresses via share-manifest feeds).\n\nSettings UI components read from `window.ph.swarm` to render stamp health, storage stats, sync badges, folder trees, and USD-denominated pricing.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
    }
  },
